  <p class=MsoNormal style='text-autospace:none'><b><a name=reverted>Q: I</a> entered Success Criteria, 
    and now my numbers have reverted to zeros in the report.  What happened?</b></p>
  <p class=MsoNormal><b>A: </b>This is usually due to the &quot;Snapshot&quot; function 
    of the “Campus Demographics” section.  Often times a staff member has included 
    the numbers one week and then the numbers haven't changed the next week, so 
    they think, &quot;Why enter them again? They haven't changed.&quot;  In reality, 
    “Campus Demographics” is only a snapshot.  These numbers are <u>NOT</u> carried 
    over from week to week. A zero is recorded for any field that is left blank.  
    When Success Criteria reports are compiled for your campus, the reports will 
    take the most recently entered &quot;campus demographics&quot; numbers within 
    the specified date range of the report.  If the most recent number is a zero, 
    the report will show a zero.  </p>
